OL,3,CWhat is the 'human statue' condition
OL,4,Cafflicting Celine Dion?
OL,6,FSPS is a rare, progressive
OL,7,Fneurological disorder of the central
OL,8,Fnervous system and affects around one
OL,9,Fin a million people, according to the
OL,10,FNational Organization for Rare
OL,11,FDisorders (NORD).
OL,13,FIf left untreated it can lead to
OL,14,Fpermanent disability or death.
OL,16,FThe symptoms usually develop slowly
OL,17,Fover several months or years, often
OL,18,Fbeginning with muscle stiffness and
OL,19,Fdiscomfort which can come and go - but
OL,20,Fthe stiffness gradually becomes fixed.
